1. Revisiting Lab 2

Code 
library(tidyverse) 
library(here) 

# read in data
surveys <- read_csv(here('labs', 'lab_5', 'surveys.csv')) 

# change formats to factor
surveys <- surveys |> 
  mutate(species = factor(species),
         day_of_week = factor(day_of_week))

# Revised 3/19/2022 - Modified transparency and fixed axes labels
# make plot
ggplot(data = surveys,
       mapping = aes(x = weight, 
                      y = fct_reorder(
                        .f = species, 
                        .x = weight, 
                        .fun = 'median',
                        ))) +  
        geom_jitter(color = "darkseagreen", alpha = .1) +
        geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0) +
        labs(x = "Weight (g)",
             title = "Rodent Species Weights",
             y = "")

2. Time Series Plot

Code 
surveys |> 
  group_by(genus, year) |> 
  summarize(mean_weight = mean(weight)) |>
  ungroup()  |>
ggplot(mapping = aes(x = year,
                  y = mean_weight,
                  color = fct_reorder(.f = genus, 
                                      .x = mean_weight, 
                                      .desc = TRUE ))) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_discrete(name = "Rodent Genus") +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank()) +
  labs(title = "Average Rodent Weight (in grams) Over Time",
       x = "Year")

3. Captures over the Week

Code 
# Revised 3/19/2022 Fixed axis labels, switched to geom_bar
days_levels <- c(
  "Sun", "Sat", "Fri", "Thu", "Wed", "Tue", "Mon"
  )

ggplot(data = surveys,
       mapping = aes(
         y = factor(day_of_week, levels = days_levels))) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(title = "Number of Rodents Captured on Each Day of the Week ",
       y = "")

Code 
ggplot(data = surveys,
       mapping = aes(
         y = fct_collapse(day_of_week,
                          "weekend" = c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri"),
                          "weekday" = c("Sat", "Sun")))) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(title = "Number of Rodents Captured on Weekends vs. Weekdays",
       y = "")

## 1. Revisiting Lab 2

```{r}
library(tidyverse) 
library(here) 

# read in data
surveys <- read_csv(here('labs', 'lab_5', 'surveys.csv')) 

# change formats to factor
surveys <- surveys |> 
  mutate(species = factor(species),
         day_of_week = factor(day_of_week))

# Revised 3/19/2022 - Modified transparency and fixed axes labels
# make plot
ggplot(data = surveys,
       mapping = aes(x = weight, 
                      y = fct_reorder(
                        .f = species, 
                        .x = weight, 
                        .fun = 'median',
                        ))) +  
        geom_jitter(color = "darkseagreen", alpha = .1) +
        geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0) +
        labs(x = "Weight (g)",
             title = "Rodent Species Weights",
             y = "")
```

## 3. Captures over the Week

```{r}
# Revised 3/19/2022 Fixed axis labels, switched to geom_bar
days_levels <- c(
  "Sun", "Sat", "Fri", "Thu", "Wed", "Tue", "Mon"
  )

ggplot(data = surveys,
       mapping = aes(
         y = factor(day_of_week, levels = days_levels))) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(title = "Number of Rodents Captured on Each Day of the Week ",
       y = "")
         
ggplot(data = surveys,
       mapping = aes(
         y = fct_collapse(day_of_week,
                          "weekend" = c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri"),
                          "weekday" = c("Sat", "Sun")))) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(title = "Number of Rodents Captured on Weekends vs. Weekdays",
       y = "")
```
